      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of same lot material; geometric inputs from CMM measurements.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V ELI) elastic modulus and yield strength were derived from tensile coupon tests on material from the same manufacturing lot as the test constructs. Geometric dimensions were verified by CMM measurements on three representative screws. UHMWPE block properties sourced from supplier datasheet with documented uncertainty bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N ≥ 10 test constructs from production lots; sample representativeness documented.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled from production-representative components across two independent laboratories (N=6 Lab A, N=5 Lab B). Sample selection followed a stratified approach covering the expected dimensional tolerance range. Lot traceability was maintained throughout."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of COU loading environments including at least two load magnitudes or displacement rates.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single displacement rate (5 mm/min) per ASTM F1717. Although this rate is standard for quasi-static characterization, it does not span the range of physiological loading rates relevant to the broader COU. Achieved level 2 reflects this limitation; the shortfall was accepted given that rate sensitivity of titanium alloy constructs is negligible in the quasi-static regime."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
