      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA input parameters demonstrably matched to experimental specimen measurements; deviations quantified.",
      "rationale": "FEA models were individualized to each test construct using CMM-measured geometry for the rod and screw bodies. Material properties were assigned from lot-specific coupon data. Boundary conditions replicated the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry as measured. Residual parameter equivalency uncertainty was propagated into uval."
    },
    {
