      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using ASME V&V 10.1 area metric; E/uval reported for all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for stiffness (1.12), yield force (1.41), and force at 40 mm displacement (0.98). All values below 1.96 threshold. Percent differences were 5.1%, 8.3%, and 4.7% respectively. Validation uncertainty uval incorporated experimental measurement uncertainty, model input uncertainty, and numerical solution error via RSS combination."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to the clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly relevant to clinical performance assessment of pedicle screw constructs. These QoIs are required in the FDA 510(k) submission pathway for spinal fixation systems and map directly to the risk of construct failure leading to revision surgery."
    },
